    $post->likes_count = $post->likes()->count();

    return view('posts.show', [
        'post' => $post
    ]);
}
```

The method signature shows:
- `Request $request` - The HTTP request object
- `Post $post` - A Post model instance that is automatically resolved from the route parameter

The route parameter `{post}` will be automatically resolved by Laravel's route model binding to a `Post` model instance. This means there's a path parameter named `post` which is required and represents the ID or slug of the post.

